 2020}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/judgementall-hai-kya-box-office-collection-kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-raos-film-earns-rs-31-cr-7099651.html|title=Judgementall Hai Kya box office collection: Kangana Ranaut, Rajkummar Rao's film earns Rs 31 cr in opening week- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2 August 2019|website=Firstpost}}</ref> film directed by [[Prakash Kovelamudi]], with screenplay by [[Kanika Dhillon]] starring [[Rajkummar Rao]] and [[Kangana Ranaut]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kangana-ranaut-kanika-dhillon-mental-kya-hai-writer-5360921/|title=People warned me not to work with Kangana Ranaut: Kanika Dhillon|date=18 September 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/mental-hai-kya-rajkummar-rao-kangana-ranaut-shooting-photos-5180284/|title=Mental Hai Kya: Rajkummar Rao, Kangana Ranaut start shooting|date=17 May 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Produced by [[Ekta Kapoor]], the film was theatrically released in India on 26 July 2019.<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/kangana-ranaut-to-clash-with-hrithik-roshan-at-box-office-as-mental-hai-kya-release-gets-shifted-2131137.html|title=It's Kangana Ranaut Versus Hrithik Roshan on July 26|date=7 May 2019|work=News18|access-date=7 May 2019|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/mental-hai-kya-new-motion-posters-suggest-no-change-in-title-of-kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-rao-s-film-see-pics/story-whpbeyqAdBR7s0CeOWnxPI.html|title=Mental Hai Kya: New motion posters suggest no change in title of Kangana Ranaut-Rajkummar Rao's film |date=23 June 2019|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|access-date=23 June 2019|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nBobby is a strange wealthy young woman living alone in [[Mumbai]] and working as a dubbing artist. In childhood, she had interfered in a fight between her parents, causing them to fall off the terrace to their deaths. When a producer touches her at work, she reacts by slicing his nose with a knife. She is then sent to an asylum. Her uncle manages her property and offers her house as a rental to a young married couple. Keshav is the husband to Reema. Bobby is obsessed with the couple and spies and stalks them constantly. Reema dies in a fire in the kitchen when a bottle of pesticide explodes. Bobby suspects Keshav and tries to get the police to investigate him but they find no evidence. She hallucinates Keshav threatening her and hits him with a chair in front of the police. She is put back in the asylum. It is revealed that she is imagining things; during electric shock treatment, she remembers that she threw the pesticide on the wife because she hallucinated a cockroach on her.\n\nTwo years later, Bobby is taking her meds but not leaving her house. Her cousin in London arranges for Bobby to be an understudy in a re-imagining of the [[Ramayana]] that she is helping design. When Bobby meets her cousin's new husband, it turns out to be Keshav. Keshav warns his wife that Bobby is not stable but his wife does not believe him. Bobby starts to lose herself in the character of Sita that she is understudying. She believes Keshav is Raavan and it is up to her to defeat him. Keshav panics and reaches out to her old boyfriend, Varun, who confirms that she obsesses over things and had imagined him to be a criminal. He breaks into her house and finds boxes of photos with Bobby photoshopped in instead of Keshav's wife. A photo of Keshav's wedding to her cousin proves that Bobby knew beforehand that they were married.\n\nKeshav confronts Bobby. The next morning, he tells his wife that Bobby tried to kiss him, and she in turn tells his wife that he tried to rape her. When she later sees Keshav backstage, she grabs an ax and chases him, cutting a rope that sends a light falling. Afraid she has hurt someone, she goes on the run and gains three hallucinatory friends. They take her to a library, where she researches Keshav and thinks she has found evidence that he is a serial killer who takes on new identities and kills his wives. She returns to the house to confront him, dressed as Sita, ties up her pregnant cousin and when Keshav arrives, threatens him. Keshav tries to reason with her before revealing that he IS indeed a serial killer. He even killed his first wife, throwing the match on her after Bobby covered her in pesticide. Bobby fights him and she and her cousin are both saved when Keshav is burnt alive in the same manner in which his victims burned to death. At the end, she strides down the street in London surrounded by her hallucinations proudly declaring that she is what she is and will not change.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Rajkummar Rao]] as Keshav Kumar\n*[[Kangana Ranaut]] as Bobby Grewal\n*[[Jimmy Shergill]] as Shridhar Awasthi<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/jimmy-shergill-joins-kangana-ranauts-mental-hai-kya/articleshow/64753487.cms|title=Jimmy Shergill joins Kangana Ranaut's Mental Hai Kya|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Amyra Dastur]] as Reema Kumar (nee Agnihotri)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/amyra-dastur-joins-rajkummar-rao-kangana-ranaut-in-mental-hai-kya/story-wTgJscKrXiNCfpGzpN0BzI.html|title=Amyra Dastur joins Rajkummar Rao, Kangana Ranaut in Mental Hai Kya|date=23 May 2018|website=hindustan times|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Amrita Puri]] as Megha Kumar\n*[[Kanika Dhillon]] as Sita\n* [[Brijendra Kala]] as Officer Ram Pandey\n* [[Satish Kaushik]] as Officer Durjan Deshmukh<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/satish-kaushik-joins-kangana-ranaut-and-rajkummar-rao-in-mental-hai-kya/articleshow/64392199.cms|title=Satish Kaushik joins Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao in Mental Hai Kya|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Lalit Behl]] as Uncle\n*[[Hussain Dalal]] as Varun Bahl\n<!--As this film has not been released, any additions to this section must be sourced per WP:CRYSTAL-->\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Filming ===\nPrincipal photography of the film began on 16 May 2018, in Mumbai.<ref name=\":0\"/> After completing the shooting in Mumbai, the production team went to London for next schedule. The film [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] on 9 July 2018 in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-rao-mental-hai-kya-5252220/|title=Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao wrap up Mental Hai Kya|date=9 July 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Judgementall Hai Kya\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Arjuna Harjai]], [[Rachita Arora]], [[Tanishk Bagchi]] and Daniel B. George\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 20 July 2019 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/judgementall-hai-kya/Y0P1rL-PNck|title= Judgementall Hai Kya - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack |publisher=Jio Saavn}}</ref>\n| recorded     = 2018-2019\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 14:44\n| language     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| label        = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| year         = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|8mxdk-cloz4|Official Audio Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n\nThe music of the film is composed by [[Arjuna Harjai]], [[Rachita Arora]], [[Tanishk Bagchi]] and Daniel B. George while lyrics are written by Prakhar Varunendra, [[Kumaar]], Tanishk Bagchi, Raja Kumari and Prakahar Vihaan. Background music scored by Daniel B George.\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline = Track listing \n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 14:44\n| title1 = The Wakhra Swag \n| extra1 = Navv Inder, [[Lisa Mishra]]<br>'''Rap:''' [[Raja Kumari]]\n| music1 = [[Tanishk Bagchi]]\n| lyrics1 = Tanishk Bagchi, Raja Kumari\n| length1 = 3:16\n| title2 = Para Para\n| extra2 = Arun Dev Yadav\n| music2 = [[Rachita Arora]] \n| lyrics2 = Prakhar Varunendra\n| length2 = 3:51\n| title3  = Judgementall Hai Kya\n| extra3  = Jaspreet Jasz, Rachita Arora, Nivedita Padmanabhan\n| music3  = Rachita Arora\n| lyrics3 = Prakhar Varunendra\n| length3 = 2:46\n| title4  = Kis Raste Hai Jana\n| extra4  = Surabhi Dashputra, [[Arjuna Harjai]]\n| music4  = Arjuna Harjai\n| lyrics4 = [[Kumaar]]\n| length4 = 3:31\n| title5  = Kar Samna\n| extra5  = Amir Khan, [[Brijesh Shandilya]], Protijyoti Ghosh, Daniel B. George\n| music5  = Daniel B. George\n| lyrics5 = Prakhar Vihaan\n| length5 = 1:20\n}}\n\n==Marketing and release==\n\nOn 4 March 2018, producer Ekta Kapoor revealed the first two posters of the film on Twitter, each depicting the two leads - a cross-eyed Ranaut and Rao holding up his middle fingers to his eyes; Kapoor hinted at the theme of mental instability by captioning, \"It's time to bring out the crazy in you... Because Sanity is overrated!\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/mental-hai-kya-ekta-kapoor-unveils-first-look-of-upcoming-film-starring-kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-rao-4376863.html|title=Mental Hai Kya: Ekta Kapoor unveils first-look of upcoming film starring Kangana Ranaut, Rajkummar Rao- Entertainment News, Firstpost|work=Firstpost|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> In an interview, writer Kanika Dhillon called the film a \"quirky thriller\" <ref>{{cite web | title = Judgemental Hai Kya is quirky! - Kanika Dhillon |publisher=Kovid Gupta Films| url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ryCuVv99C8&t=1s|date=2019| accessdate = 25 June 2019 }}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, Balaji Motion Pictures released two more first look posters, depicting both lead characters at crime scenes. The following day, 6 March, another two posters for the film were released, with leads Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao posing in \"quirky\" and dangerous positions- a knife-wielding Ranaut in a water-filled bathtub surrounded by electronic gadgets at its edge, and Rao holding a butcher knife and cutting an apple, with blood seeping from his hand.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/mental-hai-kya-rajkummar-rao-kangana-ranaut-first-look-5086654/|title=Mental Hai Kya third look: Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao are killing it|date=7 March 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 October 2018, the producers released a new poster, a composite of the original two posters of a cross-eyed Ranaut and Rao holding up his middle fingers, to reveal the film's release date.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/mental-hai-kya-release-date-kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-rao-5398015/|title=Mental Hai Kya: Kangana Ranaut, Rajkummar Rao starrer to release on March 29, 2019|date=11 October 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=12 October 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Release date of the film is changed to 21 June 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-rao-starrer-mental-hai-kya-release-june-21-2019/|title=Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao starrer Mental Hai Kya to release on June 21, 2019|date=17 April 2019|website=Bollywood Hungama|language=en|access-date=17 April 2019}}</ref> Rao announced the new date on his Twitter account along with new poster of the film.<ref name=\":2\"/> The release date was further extended to 26 July 2019 on 7 May 2019 by [[Balaji Motion Pictures]].<ref name=\":9\"/>\n\nThe film promotions were also wrapped in controversy as the lead actress, Kangana Ranaut, apparently questioned a journalist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/kangana-ranaut-gets-into-an-ugly-fight-with-a-journalist-during-judgementall-hai-kya-song-launch/articleshow/70122135.cms|title=Kangana Ranaut gets into an ugly fight with a journalist during 'Judgementall Hai Kya' song launch - Times of India \u25ba|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=27 July 2019}}</ref> for his personal remarks about her and also Rani of Jhansi. The incident took an uglier turn as the Entertainment Journalists' Guild of India decided to boycott<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/entertainment-journalists-to-boycott-kangana-ranaut-after-spat-with-reporter-at-judgemental-hai-kya-event-1565647-2019-07-10|title=Entertainment journalists to boycott Kangana Ranaut after spat with reporter at Judgemental Hai Kya event|last=DelhiJuly 10|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=July 10|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=27 July 2019|last3=Ist|first3=2019 10:43}}</ref> Kangana Ranaut until she issued an unconditional apology. The producer of the film Ekta Kapoor issued an unconditional apology on behalf of her.\n\nIn June 2019, the film's title was changed to ''Judgementall Hai Kya'' due to objections from [[Indian Psychiatric Society]] (IPS) which filed a complaint to the [[Central Board of Film Certification]] (CBFC) claiming that the original title, ''Mental Hai Kya'', trivialises mental health issues.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao's 'Mental Hai Kya'' is now 'Judgemental Hai Kya' {{!}} Hindi Movie News - Bollywood - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/hindi/kangana-ranaut-and-rajkummar-raos-mental-hai-kya-is-now-judgemental-hai-kya/videoshow/70000891.cms |accessdate=29 June 2019 |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=29 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Panchal |first1=Komal RJ |title=Kangana-Rajkummar starrer Mental Hai Kya is now Judgementall Hai Kya |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/kangana-ranaut-starrer-now-titled-judgemental-hai-kya-mental-hai-kya-5806140/ |accessdate=29 June 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |date=29 June 2019 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Judgementall Hai Kya: Kangana Ranaut's film gets new title after criticism from mental health experts- Entertainment News, Firstpost |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/judgemental-hai-kya-kangana-ranauts-film-gets-new-title-after-criticism-from-mental-health-experts-6901931.html |accessdate=29 June 2019 |work=[[Firstpost]] |date=29 June 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 July official trailer of the film was launched by [[Balaji Motion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=BywLe4m2j2I|title= Judgementall Hai Kya Official Trailer - Kangana Ranaut, Rajkummar Rao - 26th July 2019|publisher=BalajiMotionPictures|website=YouTube|date=2 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/judgemental-hai-kya-trailer-the-kangana-ranaut-and-rajkummar-rao-starrer-is-a-crazy-and-fun-filled-ride/articleshow/70045339.cms|title=Judgemental Hai Kya' trailer: The Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao starrer is a crazy and fun-filled ride|website=Times of India |date=2 July 2019|access-date=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film has been certified with a runtime of 116 minutes by [[British Board of Film Classification]] and was released on 26 July 2019.<ref name=BBFC />\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nOn [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rating of 62% based on thirteen reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6.67/10.<ref name=\":cr1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/judgementall_hai_kya|title=JUDGEMENTALL HAI KYA|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]]|accessdate=27 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nSreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film 3.5/5 stars, found Kovelamudi's narrative style as 'quirky and edgy'. Praising performance of [[Kangana Ranaut]], termed it as \"brilliant\", as for [[Rajkummar Rao]] she felt that he fitted into 'his slightly macho, edgy persona like a glove'. Concluding she opines, \"''Judgementall Hai Kya'' keeps the element of suspense alive all the way till the end, as it pushes the envelope as a dark, psychological whodunit, with a social message weaved in that can\u2019t be ignored.\" <ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-details/mental-hai-kya/movieshow/63166514.cms|title=Judgementall Hai Kya|work=The Times of India|first=Sreeparna|last=Sengupta|date=25 July 2019|access-date=25 July 2019}}</ref> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' gave the film 2.5/5 stars, found the plot to be confusing and stated that the makers have done very poor research on mental health. The movie, at certain points, makes fun of issues that require serious attention. Psychological disorders are a concern and such toxic take can only push people back. The performances are great, especially that of Rajkumar Rao, who unfortunately is caught in between a poor script. Kangana's performance is also decent but she could have done better.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/judgementall-hai-kya-movie-review-kangana-rajkummars-unfettered-performances-suffer-a-confusing-plot-and-poor-research-on-mental-health-7059841.html|title=Judgementall Hai Kya movie review: Kangana, Rajkummar's unfettered performances suffer a confusing plot and poor research on mental health- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=26 July 2019|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=27 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nRaja Sen of ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' gave 4/5 stars and felt that the slick, snappy looking comedy has more to offer, as a 'smart, significant satire'. Praising the performances he said, \"This is a finely acted film, with superb performances from Amrita Puri, Satish Kaushik and Jimmy Sheirgill, not to mention Rao, but it rests entirely on Ranaut\u2019s shoulders and she delivers both vitality and credibility.\" Concluding he recommended to watch the film as 'carrying homilies on placards' and opined, \"It is a film about malicious misdirection, and the validity of our narratives \u2014 especially those labelled incorrect. It\u2019s okay to jump at a cockroach even if you\u2019re the only one who sees it. A bug can be a feature.\"<ref>{{cite news|first=Raja|last=Sen|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/judgementall-hai-kya-movie-review-kangana-ranaut-dazzles-in-a-film-about-mind-games/story-yFXyYBru3CmqFlELhKznkL_amp.html|title=Judgementall Hai Kya movie review: Kangana Ranaut dazzles in a film about mind games|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=26 July 2019 |accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref> Gaurang Chauhan of ''[[Times Now]]'' rating the film with 3/5 stars terms it as 'one of its kind film', praising the performances of lead of Ranaut and Rao and supporting cast of [[Hussain Dalal]], [[Satish Kaushik]] and [[Brijendra Kala]] says, \" This movie belongs to [Ranaut] and she simply nails it.\" In conclusion, he opines, \"Do give this one a try for its uniqueness, eccentricity, jaw-dropping moments, technical brilliance and Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao's phenomenal performances. Watch it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/reviews/movies/article/judgementall-hai-kya-movie-review-kangana-ranaut-and-rajkummar-rao-starrer-is-one-of-its-kind-bizarre-fun/458999|title=Judgementall Hai Kya Movie Review: Kangana Ranaut and Rajkummar Rao starrer is one of its kind, bizarre fun|website=Times Now News|date=26 July 2019|access-date=26 July 2019}}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]] of [[CNN-IBN]] stated, \"While you admire the attempt at originality, you can\u2019t help feeling frustrated at just how it all comes apart in the end.\" He praised the performances, and termed Ranaut as solid. But, he felt that the film fell short of greatness because of a muddled script and gave 2.5/5 stars.<ref>{{cite web |title=Judgementall Hai Kya Movie Review: Kangana Ranaut, Rajkummar Rao Film Falls Way Short of Greatness |url=https://www.news18.com/amp/news/movies/judgementall-hai-kya-movie-review-kangana-ranaut-rajkummar-rao-film-falls-way-short-of-greatness-2247893.html |website=News18 |accessdate=27 July 2019 |date=26 July 2019 |author=Rajeev Masand}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\nAccording to the ''[[Bollywood Hungama]]'' opening day collection of the film is {{INR}}4.20 crore and the second day collection is {{INR}}7 crore, whereas third day collection is {{INR}}7.70 crore. The opening weekend gross is {{INR}}26.97 crore worldwide.<ref name=\"boxoff\"/>\n\n{{As of|2019|08|16}}, with a gross of {{INR}}39.42 crore in India and {{INR}}5.50 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}44.92 crore.<ref name=\"topg\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2019/ |title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide |website=Bollywood Hungama |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|tt8108196}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/judgementall-hai-kya/ Judgementall Hai Kya] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|judgementall_hai_kya}}\n\n{{Balaji Telefilms}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Balaji Motion Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n[[Category:Indian black comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about psychiatry]]\n[[Category:Mental illness in films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language black comedy film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Judgementall Hai Kya\n| image          = Judgementall Hai Kya poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Prakash Kovelamudi]]\n| producer       = [[Ekta Kapoor]]<br />[[Shobha Kapoor]]<br />[[Shailesh R Singh]]\n| screenplay     = [[Kanika Dhillon]]\n| starring       = [[Rajkummar Rao]]<br />[[Kangana Ranaut]]\n| music          = '''Songs:'''<br />[[Arjuna Harjai]]<br />[[Rachita Arora]]<br />[[Tanishk Bagchi]]<br />Daniel B. George<br />'''Score:'''<br />Daniel B. George\n| cinematography = [[Pankaj Kumar (cinematographer)|Pankaj Kumar]]\n| editing        = Shweta Venkat Matthew<br />Sheeba Sehgal<br />Prashanth Ramachandran\n| studio         = [[Balaji Motion Pictures]]<br />Karma Media and Entertainment<br />ALT Entertainment\n| distributor    = Pen Marudhar Entertainment<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://boxofficeindia.co.in/pen-marudhar-entertainment-acquires-india-distribution-rights-these-balaji-films|title=Pen Marudhar Entertainment acquires the India Distribution rights of these Balaji films|date=17 June 2019|work=Box office India|access-date=17 June 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|26|df=y|ref1=<ref name=\":9\" />}}\n| runtime        = 116 minutes<ref name=BBFC>{{cite web | url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/judgementall-hai-kya-2019 | title=Judgementall Hai Kya | website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] | accessdate=23 July 2019}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = {{INR}}29\u201350 crore<ref>{{cite news |title=Judgementall Hai Kya box office collection Day 1: New film struggles to fight The Lion King |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/judgementall-hai-kya-box-office-collection-day-1-new-film-struggles-to-fight-the-lion-king-1574113-2019-07-27 |accessdate=27 July 2019 |work=India Today |date=27 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Judgementall Hai Kya box office collection Day 7: Kangana Ranaut, Rajkummar Rao's film slows down, earns Rs 31 crore|url=https://m.businesstoday.in/story/judgementall-hai-kya-box-